100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 30, 1925, tensions escalated in the Middle East as the British government faced backlash over its handling of the Palestine situation, with increasing violence reported in Jerusalem. In the United States, the Supreme Court ruled that the federal government had the authority to regulate interstate commerce, a decision anticipated to impact various industries. Meanwhile, in Europe, economic challenges persisted as nations struggled to stabilize their currencies in the post-war era.
